      • send

        public void send​(java.io.OutputStream network)
        Construct the outgoing server response. Check if status code is set, if yes write it into the output stream Write all header information into the output stream Add the content lastly and flush/close the output stream INFO: every string that gets written into the network needs a linefeed! -> Add "\r\n" to every string
        Specified by:
        send in interface BIF.SWE1.interfaces.Response
        Parameters:
        network - the output stream that will be send to the client as response
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - on set content but not set content type
        java.io.IOException - on output stream error
